		<h2>Testing notes</h2>
	  	<p class="comment default">All the below should take the default width, or the small width if defined. Also, gutter removal is deliberately unimplemented</p>

	  	<p class="comment device-width-mq">Responds to device width, not window size, so on desktop won't change appearance unless using useragent overrides
	  		
	  	</p>
	  	<p class="comment width-mq">
	  		Should have a fluid transition from one mq breakpoint to the next (i.e. each layout (except for XL) has a maximum width equal to the next largest breakpoint)
	  	</p>
		<p class="comment non-fluid">
			Should have a jerky transition from one mq breakpoint to the next (i.e. each layout has a maximum width smaller than the next largest breakpoint)
		</p>

		<div class="comment resized">
			<p>Should be resized according to the following settings</p>
			<pre><code>
				// Page widths
				$o-grid-min-width: 240px;
				$o-grid-small-max-width: 400px;
				$o-grid-medium-max-width: 580px;
				$o-grid-large-max-width: 760px;
				$o-grid-extra-large-max-width: 1160px;

				// Breakpoints
				$o-grid-small-to-medium-break: 400px;
				$o-grid-medium-to-large-break: 800px;
				$o-grid-large-to-extra-large-break: 1200px;

				//gutters
				$o-grid-responsive-half-gutter: 5px;
				$o-grid-default-half-gutter: 0.5%;
				$o-grid-fixed-half-gutter: 2px;
			</code></pre>
		</div>
		<p class="comment disabled">
			Should demonstrate responsive behaviour, but the XL breakpoint is disabled, so the widths should show in red
		</p>
